Package cs2030s.fp

Class InfiniteList<T>

java.lang.Object
cs2030s.fp.InfiniteList<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
InfiniteList.End
public class InfiniteList<T> extends Object
Recursive InfiniteList that may contain a value of type T, encapsulated in Actually class.

Value represented either with an Actually.Success or Actually.Failure, negating NullPointerException.

Computed values will be Memo-ized so that there will not be any future computations.

    • filter

      public InfiniteList<T> filter(Immutator<Boolean,? super T> pred)
      Filters out elements in the list that fail a given Immutator function. It will mark any filtered (i.e. removed or missing) element as Actually.err() instead of null. The resulting (lazily) filtered InfiniteList is returned.
      Parameters:
      pred - Predicate function that checks if the condition is met in each element.
      Returns:
      a new InfiniteList of type T.

    • limit
